<MELItem itemNbr="24-22-03" id="X-BOEING:FTID:81205.787.DDG.CU.MEL.2-24-22-03.1.2-24-22-03">
<Title>APU Generator Control Unit (AGCU)</Title>
<MELSubItem itemNbr="24-22-03-01">
<Title>Left AGCU</Title>
<DispatchCondition repairInterval="C" nbrInstalled="1" nbrRequired="0" maintIndicator="(M)" opsIndicator="(O)">
<DispatchConditionRemarks>
<Para>May be inoperative provided:</Para>
<List listType="a.">
<ListItem>
<Para>Left AGCU is deactivated.</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>APU operates normally.</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>APU battery operates normally.</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>APU SPU operates normally.</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>Right ASG generator operates normally.</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>Right ASG starter operates normally.</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>VFSG systems operate normally.</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>EDTO beyond 180 minutes is not conducted.</Para>
</ListItem>
</List>
</DispatchConditionRemarks>
<Note>
<Para>The airplane must also be dispatched using MEL item 24-22-02-02.</Para>
</Note>
<DispatchProcedure>
<MaintenanceProcedure>
<Para>A VFSG system is considered to be operating normally if its associated status message (ELEC GEN SYS L1, L2, R1 or R2) is not displayed.</Para>
<Para>Deactivate the left AGCU (AMM DDG 24-22-03).</Para>
<List listType="1.">
<ListItem>
<Para>Open and collar P300 panel circuit breaker APU GCU-L CAPT.</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>Using a flight deck multi-function display only, open the APU GCU-L R28 circuit breaker and lock with an INOP tag.</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>Gain access to the P150 panel.</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>Disconnect, cap and stow the L ASG PMG connector (DP150P01A).</Para>
</ListItem>
</List>
</MaintenanceProcedure>
<OperationProcedure>
<Note>
<Para>Engines cannot be started using external power.</Para>
</Note>
<Note>
<Para>Simultaneous engine start is not allowed.</Para>
</Note>
<List listType="1.">
<ListItem>
<Para>EDTO beyond 180 minutes is not conducted.</Para>
<?FTID-rev start?>
<?FTID-rev end?>
</ListItem>
</List>
</OperationProcedure>
</DispatchProcedure>
</DispatchCondition>
</MELSubItem>
</MELItem>
